    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Silver, ceramic or glass drinking vessels, customarily used in the Netherlands during the 17th 18th century to toast pregnant women. When the cup is filled, the figure of an infant appears from a chamber.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
